I purchased a ten piece chicken for $16. I asked for some side sauces to accompany my meal. The young Lady gave me #2 and I requested an additional sauce of another favor. She refused to give me #2. This young Lady and her counterpart working the front desk were both rude and dismissive. I spoke to the manager Victor and confirmed that NO customer should be spoken to in manner. 1. I'm a repeat customer. 2. I purchased #10 pieces of chicken and #3 sauces were clearly not enough. 3. The sauce may have cost 5 cents at the most. I tried to charge me for the sauce. Clearly 5 cents is not enough to insight argument with customers who have spent money with Popeyes. And repeat customers at that. I was very disappointed that I had to go through all this for an extra item of sauce. This location of Popeyes needs to understand the importance of customer service and neighborhood respect. I will NOT visit this location again.
